title.narrative: MATERNAL AND NEWBORN HEALTH & Prevention of Mother to Child Transmission of HIV (PMTCT)

description.narrative: Improved capacity to provide integrated MNH/PMTCT/EID services accessed by pregnant, lactating women and newborns in 14 targeted underserved counties, and during emergency situations., which contributes to Health And Emergencies, Maternal And Newborn Health, Pmtct And Infant Male Circumcision. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The most vulnerable children and women access a minimum social protection package

title.narrative: Improved capacity to provide integrated MNH/PMTCT/EID services accessed by pregnant, lactating women and newborns in 14 targetedunderserved counties, and during emergency situations.

description.narrative: 98,727 pregnant women conducted at least one ANC visit, representing 72% of the annual target. Progress was also made to raise awareness on HIV/AIDS and promote uptake of the PMTCT services. Acceptance of HIV testing among pregnant women after health education had been increased from 30% in 2014 to 95%. | Status:Constrained | As-of Date:31/12/2015
